{
  "texts": [
    "Yang et al. (2024) enhanced student agency in a postgraduate course, where learners independently explored tasks using chat logs and journals.",
    "Students who took an active role in their learning (e.g., resourceful and reflective approaches) were more likely to benefit from GenAI, while those who were passive/ receptive or resistant may not fully leverage its potential.",
    "Hu et al. (2024) introduced an AI Learning Companion that provides tailored, autonomous support, while Allen et al. (2024) presented Q-Module-Bot, enabling students to seek answers independently.",
    "Guo et al. (2024) offered EFL students AIgenerated exercises for self-paced learning.",
    "These studies have underscored GenAI's potential to empower learning autonomy and learner agency."
  ]
}